This directory contains projects I would like to highlight. Please see short notes regarding each one below.

swift/NightfallSwift: This is an example of a short game exercises practices of MVVM and eventually CoreData. Though this app did not make it to the app store, it is likely more impressive than the one that did.

swift/LifeHack: This was the first project I launched into the App Store to compliment a hobby I took part in. It is a little weak in architecture, as I was not as fluent in MVVM, but made an attempt at it.

swiftui/Nightfall: Essentially the same project as NightfallSwift, but in SwiftUI. It does not yet fully follow MVVM as the Swift version does, but it is here as proof of my ability to code in SwiftUI.